<subSubSection pageNumber="366" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="366">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="366">Note:</emphasis>
An illegitimate name as it includes the whole basis of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Bupleurum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praealtum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="366">B. praealtum</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
, i.e. the Magnol description and diagnosis. As such it is automatically typified by the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Bupleurum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="praealtum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="366">B. praealtum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Stearn (in Geck &amp; Pressler, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="366">Festschr. Claus Nissen</emphasis>
: 65. 1974) reproduces (as his f. 8) the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dodoëns">Dodoens</normalizedToken>
figure that is the type of both names.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
